eventTranslations.name: Strategic Innovation Leadership
eventTranslations.description:
This programme delivered over six days address the rate of change, the scope for adoption and disruption and the front-page successes contribute to a general belief that technology has re-written our understanding of markets, businesses, consumers, management and leadership. ​


This highly interactive course will provide the participants with conceptual knowledge and practical tools required for Managing Strategy and Innovation mediated by technology– whether executives of medium or large companies or entrepreneurs creating new companies. We’ll examine the (sometimes hidden) drivers behind how digital technologies are transforming business context across products, services, value chain and industry structures and the universal principles that can be applied to manage in this environment. ​


The programme will offer advanced perspectives on Strategy, Leadership, Innovation, Knowledge Management, and Privacy and IP. Combined these topics provide a granular understanding of some of the major challenges facing strategy and innovation.​


Outcomes of this programme will include the participants ability to ​

  • Analyse and understand your organisational and industry position and how it is being impacted and transformed by technology now and over the next number of years. ​
  • Identify emerging trends in industry and their impact on business processes and value creation ​
  • Define plans for action to successfully transform your business and complete in new markets and using new or hybrid business models. ​
  • Make strategic decisions around the use of digital technology, understanding how to create and capture new business value for your organisation ​
  • Create and evaluate new business models ​
  • Understand how to execute Innovation Transformation ​
  • Successfully manage change through transformation.​
eventTranslations.summary: The programme will offer advanced perspectives on Strategy, Leadership, Innovation, Knowledge Management, and Privacy and IP.

eventTranslations.name: Innovating in a Virtual/Hybrid Workplace
eventTranslations.description:
Pre-covid most innovation was conducted in an in-person environment. With the growth of remote and distributed teams there is a need for new approaches to enable these teams to innovate effectively. ​


This 1 to 2 day workshop will look at how companies can innovate effectively in virtual and hybrid workplaces, delivering skills to ​


This workshop covers​

  • Challenges and opportunities of leadership, culture and technology in virtual and hybrid environments​
  • Cognitive bias that inhibit virtual and hybrid innovation ​
  • Approaches to asynchronous and synchronous innovation in virtual and hybrid environments. Virtual v’s in person ideation and idea generation.​
  • Serendipity in asynchronous environments​
  • Methods tools, mindsets and skills for remote virtual and hybrid innovation development including prototyping, research techniques, customer mapping, service design, blueprinting, creativity etc. ​
  • A roadmap for successful implementation
eventTranslations.summary: With the growth of remote and distributed teams there is a need for new approaches to enable these teams to innovate effectively. ​

eventTranslations.name: Design Thinking for Senior Leaders
eventTranslations.description:
This will cover training in the principles of Design Thinking, collaborative working and understanding user needs. It will support understanding how Design Thinking cultivates a growth mindset and how to create conditions to support it in the organisation. 


Delivered over two days. ​


Topics covered will include 

  • Growth Mindset
  • User centred design and innovation
  • Rapid, repeated Learning Experiments
  • 4‐Factor framework for project success
  • Ethnographic observations and user interviews. 


Leaders will also undertake an exercise to query the status quo assumptions of embedded ways of working in their organisations. Facilitator led discussions will help leaders explore how to cultivate and sustain a growth mindset in their organisation.
eventTranslations.summary: This programme will cover training in the principles of Design Thinking, collaborative working and understanding user needs.

eventTranslations.name: Intellectual Property and the Innovation Pipeline
eventTranslations.description:
This two day hands on workshop focus on IP Strategy emphasises the importance of securing the full range of RD&I related IP assets (including patents, designs, trade secrets, copyright, trademarks etc) and deploying them strategically for the benefit of the business. The development of an effective IP strategy can assist companies in achieving their growth targets.​


This workshop seeks to assist companies to address common issues of:​

  • low IP awareness​
  • limited internal IP management capability​
  • the cost of obtaining external IP expertise​


It will also deal with the real world implications of managing intellectual property on a day to day basis and provide attendees with a framework on which to build and implement a commercially effective IP Strategy.​


​
eventTranslations.summary: The development of an effective IP strategy can assist companies in achieving their growth targets.​

eventTranslations.name: Accelerating Product Development
eventTranslations.description:
This programme is offered in a series of event ranging from ½ day to two days and is customisable to specific organisation needs. ​


  • Why most new products fail – why a few really do well; and why some business are stars in new-product development – the majority are not​
  • How to build these “success factors” into your new product process and methods​
  • Creating that unique superior product with a compelling value proposition… the #1 success driver​
  • Iterative Development to get much better VoC (voice of customer) input and get the product right ​
  • Accelerating new products to market: three of the best ways​
  • Using Agile and Lean methods to accelerate and improve your new product system​
  • Avoiding pipeline overload – too many projects underway, learning to say “No” – gates with teeth​
  • Project prioritization – using the Productivity Index – to maximize your yield from R&D ​
  • Project selection – using Value-Based portfolio management to pick the best projects for Development​
  • Resourcing estimation and planning leading to resourcing projects properly​
eventTranslations.summary: This programme is offered in a series of events ranging from ½ day to two days and is customisable to specific organisation needs.

eventTranslations.name: Journey to Service Design Mastery​
eventTranslations.description:
The new services landscape is unlocking innovation opportunities in nearly every industry. But how are these services created? Always with the best intentions, but quite often missing the mark.​

​

To enable industries to design and deliver their services with a human-centred approach, Service Design as a practice has been established. It's about the shaping of service experiences so that they really work for people. Removing the lumps and bumps that make them frustrating, and then adding some magic to make them compelling.​

​

“When you have two coffee shops right next to each other, and each sells the exact same coffee at the exact same price, service design is what makes you walk into one and not the other.” — 31Volts Service Design Studio​

​

In this course you won't learn about creating delightful experiences. Obviously, those experiences are amazing things to aim for, but in reality, so many services are created with systemic flaws. And so, instead, you will learn about a powerful tool, Journey Mapping, used to ensure that right from the start you are creating excellent functional experiences which will in turn bring you to the delightful.​

​

Too often we hear "I can create a Journey Map". Sure, most people can create a journey map. But can they create a journey map that aligns perspectives and is inclusive? Much like having access to Microsoft Word does not make you a New York Times Best Selling author, the same can be said about creating Journey Maps.​

​

Journey Mapping is one of the most powerful tools in any innovator’s toolkit.​

​

When correctly presented and created, it provides a visual representation of the experiences faced by people navigating an organisational ecosystem.​

​

In this course, we will cover all aspects of how you can use the method of 'mapping' to cover areas such as customer journey mapping, user journey mapping and employee journey mapping.
eventTranslations.summary: The new services landscape is unlocking innovation opportunities in nearly every industry. But how are these services created?

eventTranslations.name: Deepening Your Innovation Design
eventTranslations.description:
Delivered over 2 x 0.5 days or 1 day. ​


This is a deep dive into specific methods/tools/mindsets or a focus on a discrete phase of a project. This will be suited for teams with some experience of design thinking and want to build mastery in specific elements of design thinking, e.g. empathy, visualization, storytelling, prototyping, research techniques, customer mapping, service design, blueprinting, creativity etc.​


Each attendee will receive a copy of the book, ‘Experiencing Design – The Innovator’s Journey’ by Jeanne, Liedtka, Karen Hold & Jessica Eldridge​.
eventTranslations.summary: This is a deep dive into specific methods/tools/mindsets or a focus on a discrete phase of a project.

eventTranslations.name: Strategic Innovation for Sustainability
eventTranslations.description:
Sustainability and in particular tailoring your innovation activities towards a sustainability strategy, is a key element for every business.​

​

In this interactive session, learn how to tailor your research and innovation towards delivery of your Sustainability targets. 


This workshop will be covering everything from sustainability strategy to sustainable innovation – seeing how sustainability considerations (environmental, social, financial) are being integrated into all company systems including design, research and development (R&D) and day to day operations.
eventTranslations.summary: In this interactive session, learn how to tailor your research and innovation towards delivery of your Sustainability targets.

eventTranslations.name: Lean Product Innovation
eventTranslations.description:
This programme delivered over 4 days is focussed on the application and implementation of lean principles to product development. It delivers a Lean Product Development framework and set of tools and techniques that is designed to fit within an existing governance process (Stage Gate/Agile) or to stand on its own providing both a governance and execution methodology.


﻿The 3 major components of the framework cover:​

  • Picking the right problem​
  • Planning the project to accelerate development​
  • Executing the project​

 ​

The framework and tools can be customised and deliver 4 game changers in organisations’ NPD systems, including:​

  1. A front-end discovery framework to support the identification and selection of winning ideas for your business and customers. ​
  2. Techniques to maximise valuable R&D resources to successfully design, develop and deliver significantly greater customer value and financial returns. ​
  3. Guidance on governance and product development events to accelerate your new product development pipeline, delivering up to 30% faster time to market.
eventTranslations.summary: A Lean Product Development framework and set of tools and techniques that is designed to fit within an existing governance process.

eventTranslations.name: The New System of Innovation
eventTranslations.description:
The key to delivering a winning product, service or business model innovation to the market is to identify and validate which are the ‘right’ Needs to solve for your customers. Applying a process to identify and validate which are the ‘right’ Needs to solve for target customers / markets is key to success.


The programme will include thorough training and application of the following:- 

  • Applying Needs-Led Design Thinking 
  • Understanding the mindset and skills required 
  • Working within an innovation Framework 
  • Using a dedicated Team Miro Board – to create and capture knowledge and gain key insights to support informed commercial decision-making. 


This packaged training & resource offering is the foundation for embedding a systematic Needs-Led Innovation process in an organisation. This is applied using the Discovery Team Board and where desired, supported by external consultants of your choice. 


Value for each Innovation Team - 

  • Knowledge of the Needs-led process and its value 
  • Experience in applying it to a real project (with support) 
  • A pipeline of evidence-based Needs 
  • A proven, repeatable process that can be integrated with existing processes 
  • A process aligned to ISO 56002 


Value for CEOs / Senior Teams - 

  • Process to deliver on the defined Innovation Strategy and objectives 
  • Innovation Vitality Metrics Dashboard
  • Disruptive Insights Tool: to catalogue categories of Needs and identify patterns, so no 
  • Needs or Insights are missed
  • Build An Innovation portfolio and pipeline aligned to the company’s strategy 


Duration & Format:

This programme will run 12 days over three months and is designed as a team-based programme. While this programme itself is delivered over 12 days with additional mentoring support across the three months, elements of the course can be split out across other shorter modules available through the IRDG Innovation Skillnet.


Precursor:

The Introduction to the New System of Innovation is a required precursor to this programme.  


Who should attend: 

For Innovation Champions and their project teams who have to find new and profitable growth opportunities.
eventTranslations.summary: This packaged training & resource offering is the foundation for embedding a systematic Needs-Led Innovation process in an organisation.

userProfiles.name: Mary
userProfiles.description:
Mary joined IRDG in November 2011, and has responsibility for Membership Development and Communications within the Group.


Throughout Mary’s career she has championed the role of people, learning and communications within business, engaging people in development programmes, introducing innovative communications media, and organising and hosting events and conferences to support people share experiences and learning.

userProfiles.name: Dermot
userProfiles.description:
Dermot joined IRDG in November 2021 as incoming CEO and took over in January 2022. He joined IRDG from Resolve Partners a leading Innovation Consultancy where he built accelerators, supported fundraising, and worked with founders, researchers, Universities, and Corporates.


Over his career he’s ranged from investing and supporting deep technology companies in NDRC, as COO growing Storyful from 2 to 35 staff and over a decade in technical and management roles in GE. Dermot has been an adjunct lecturer at the UCD Smurfit Graduate Business School and is a Director of the Festival of Curiosity.

userProfiles.name: Lorraine
userProfiles.description: Best employee ever.

userProfiles.name: Darragh
userProfiles.description: Darragh Gaffney is Research and Innovation Services Manager at IRDG. Darragh has many years’ experience across R&D management and a range of consultancy roles. He has a significant track record in securing multi-million € grant and funding supports across Ireland and Europe.
